19.1.hd_quote: The pressure of wanting without losing one's identity when being accepted by others.
19.1.shadow_axis: People-pleasing; identity loss to secure access.

19.2.hd_quote: The dedication of personal resources as a result of external contact.
19.2.behavioral_axis: Offers service for access to resources.
19.2.shadow_axis: Indentured dynamics; being used without true reciprocity.

19.3.hd_quote: Receptivity to approach can only be maintained through vigilance, being on guard.
19.3.behavioral_axis: Tests bargains; protects access with vigilance.

19.4.hd_quote: Individual approach which attracts and accepts cooperation.
19.4.behavioral_axis: Drives group effort when others can keep up.
19.4.shadow_axis: Frustration at othersâ€™ dependency or lagging.

19.5.hd_quote: The need to limit personal potential in order to achieve a larger goal.
19.5.behavioral_axis: May sacrifice self-interest for communal principle.

19.6.hd_quote: The avoidance of contact in general but not exclusively.
19.6.behavioral_axis: Avoids engagement unless need is legitimate.
